SIMPLE: light_year
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Light year
<hw>Light year</hw></mhw>.
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The distance over which light can
travel in a year's time in a vacuum, 5.88 trillion miles (9.46 trillion
kilometers); -- used as a unit in expressing stellar distances. It is
more than 63,000 times as great as the distance from the earth to the
sun. The star nearest to the earth's sun is about 4 light years
distant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a very large difference; -- used figuratively to
express great differences (of distance, quality, time) in
comparisons.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Although having the same rank and salary, they
were <ex>light-years</ex> apart in their ability to perform their
jobs.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lign-aloes</ent>⟦br⟧
